race.comment: TRUMPTY DUMPTY (10) has returned in good order. Easy winner first-up at Narromine then finished the race off well but was never a threat last start over 1300m at Dubbo. Back in trip but gets some weight relief so will be hard to hold out. SORRENTO PALACE (7) got a long way back and was never a factor last time out over this distance at Dubbo. Generally reliable so that run was a mystery. Must be given another chance. COMONGIN (3) started favourite but as no match for TRUMPTY DUMPTY first up over today's journey at Narromine. Lightly raced three-year-old who can improve sharply off that run and make things interesting. KEADOOL (6) led and gave a kick before being ambushed in the shadows last start over this distance at Narromine. Can run another cheeky race. ALMOST MAYBE (4) found form last start and can go on with it now.
